<Issue id="21025" key="FAB-6315" number="6315" project="10002" reporter="wlahti" assignee="wlahti" creator="wlahti" type="10001" summary="Allow log level override for submodules at peer start" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="6" created="2017-09-27 16:27:42.0" updated="2018-07-20 18:49:34.0" resolutiondate="2017-09-29 13:41:57.0" votes="0" watches="1" workflowId="40101"> <description><! CDATA Currently, it is not possible to override a submodule's log level at peer start (e.g. peer/gossip). Logic should be added to enable this.      In order to allow both yaml files and environment variables to override these levels, the submodule name should be provided in the form: {code:java} module_submodule{code} This will allow the value to be set in yaml files: {code:java} peer: gossip: warning{code} as well as via environment variables: {code:java} CORE_LOGGING_PEER_GOSSIP=warning{code}  ></description> </Issue>
